# TASK_PACKET

Task ID
CRUSHR-FORMAT-12

Title
Measure inline per-extent naming vs manifest naming for recovery gain and size cost

Role
BUILDER

Objective
Implement and compare a bounded experimental archive variant that embeds file naming information directly into each verified extent-identity record, then measure whether this restores materially better named recovery without the size blow-up of a centralized manifest-heavy design.

This packet exists because FORMAT-11 proved two things:

- distributed extent identity is extremely cheap
- distributed extent identity alone does not materially restore named recovery

The next specific hypothesis to test is:

Can embedding `name` / `path` into each local extent-identity record recover most of the naming benefit currently provided by manifest-bearing variants, while staying materially smaller than `payload_plus_manifest` and `full_current_experimental`?

This is an experiment.
It must not silently change default archive behavior.

