Hard constraints

- Do NOT weaken strict extraction semantics.
- Do NOT introduce speculative reconstruction.
- Do NOT guess filenames, paths, offsets, or ordering.
- Do NOT silently change default archive behavior.
- Keep this packet experimental and bounded.
- Deterministic behavior is required.
- Recovery may only use verified payload and verified local/distributed identity records.
- Do NOT let this packet drift into full Unix metadata preservation.
- This packet is about file naming/path truth only, not mode/uid/gid/mtime/xattrs/symlink policy.

