Required implementation scope

1) Add a new experimental variant: inline local naming

Implement a new archive variant:

extent_identity_inline_path

This variant must extend the verified per-extent identity/header record so that each extent carries enough local information to support:

- file grouping
- extent ordering
- completeness reasoning where feasible
- integrity verification linkage
- local file naming/path recovery without a separate global manifest dependency

Required local identity fields (or equivalent):
- file_id
- extent_index
- total_extent_count or equivalent completeness signal
- payload_length or extent_length
- digest / verification linkage
- logical file name or basename
- logical path or canonical archive path

The path/name fields may be encoded in whatever bounded internal format is cleanest, but the behavior must be explicit and documented.

The goal is to test the most direct version of the hypothesis:
full local naming repeated per extent.

---------------------------------------------------------------------

2) Optional compact comparison arm

If implementation is clean and bounded, also add:

extent_identity_distributed_names

This optional variant should avoid embedding the full path into every extent.
Instead, it may use:

- local per-extent identity for structure (`file_id`, ordering, verification linkage)
- a smaller distributed file-id -> path/name record repeated at controlled intervals or attached only to selected extents

This arm is OPTIONAL.
Do not add it if doing so endangers the required packet scope.

Required new variant:
- extent_identity_inline_path

Optional new variant:
- extent_identity_distributed_names

