3) Salvage support

Extend salvage to recognize and use the new naming-bearing local identity records.

Required salvage behavior for `extent_identity_inline_path`:
- group extents by file_id
- order grouped extents by extent_index
- recover named files when verified local naming survives
- recover anonymous files when structure survives but local naming does not
- classify partial ordered recovery when some extents are missing but ordering survives
- maintain existing strict verification rules

Important:
- named recovery may only occur when the path/name data used is verified and actually present
- anonymous recovery remains valid fallback behavior
- no guessed names
- no guessed path reconstruction
- no guessed missing extents

This packet specifically tests whether distributed naming can replace manifest-driven naming for the bounded salvage experiment.

