6) Size-discipline requirement

Because crushr is still a compression format, size overhead is a first-class evaluation dimension even when not the only goal.

The Markdown summary must include an explicit judgment section answering:

- Is the new variant small enough to remain credible as a compression-oriented archive design?
- Is its overhead closer to `extent_identity_only`, `payload_plus_manifest`, or `full_current_experimental`?
- Does the named-recovery gain justify the byte cost?

Do not bury this in raw tables.
